.Dd Nov 12, 2025
.Dt gufi_ls
.Os Linux
.Sh NAME
.Nm gufi_ls
.Nd GUFI version of GNU
.Xr ls 1
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op options
.Op file ...

.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a wrapper around
.Xr gufi_query 1 , which performs queries on the contents of a GUFI tree in a parallel manner. The queries that are passed into
.Xr gufi_query 1 are predefined pieces that are deterministically combined.

The input arguments and output are intended to be reminicent of GNU
.Xr ls 1 .

.Sh OPTIONS

.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It Fl -help
show this help message and exit
.It Fl v, -version
show program's version number and exit
.It Fl a, -all
do not ignore entries starting with .
.It Fl A, -almost-all
do not list implied . and ..
.It Fl -block-size SIZE
with -l, scale sizes by SIZE when printing them
.It Fl B, -ignore-backups
do not list implied entries ending with ~
.It Fl -full-time
like -l --time-style=full-iso
.It Fl G, -no-group
in a long listing, don't print group names
.It Fl h, -human-readable
with -l and -s, print sizes like 1K 234M 2G etc.
.It Fl i, -inode
print the index number of each file
.It Fl l
use a long listing format
.It Fl r, -reverse
reverse order while sorting
.It Fl R, -recursive
list subdirectories recursively
.It Fl s, -size
print the allocated size of each file, in blocks
.It Fl S
sort by file size, largest first
.It Fl -time-style\ {full-iso,iso,locale,long-iso}
time/date format with -l
.It Fl t
sort by modification time, newest first
.It Fl -delim\ c
Delimiter separating output columns
.It Fl -in-memory-name\ name
Name of in-memory database when aggregation is performed
.It Fl -aggregate-name\ name
Name of final database when aggregation is performed
.It Fl -skip-file\ filename
Name of file containing directory basenames to skip
.It Fl V, -verbose
Show the gufi_query being executed
.El

.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It EXIT_SUCCESS or EXIT_FAILURE
.El

.Pp
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width -compact
.It gufi_ls
.It @INSTALL_CONFIG@
.El

\# .Sh BUGS
\# .Sh EXAMPLE

.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr gufi_du 1 ,
.Xr gufi_getfattr 1 ,
.Xr gufi_find 1 ,
.Xr gufi_stats 1 ,
.Xr gufi_query 1
